{"Full Program Name": "The Inuit Learning and Development Program", "Program Name": "ILDP", "Level Of Government": "Government of Canada", "Administering Agency Full": "Canadian Northern Economic Development Agency", "Administering Agency": "Canadian Northern Econ. Develop.", "Delivery Agency Full": "Canadian Northern Economic Development Agency", "Delivery Agency": "Canadian Northern Econ. Develop.", "Brief Description": "The Inuit Learning and Development Program (ILDP) is a pre-employment and job training initiative aimed at helping Nunavut Inuit develop skills for potential jobs in the federal public service in Nunavut. The ILDP is a 16 month program consisting of four paid work placements lasting four months each. The objective of each work placement is to assign participants to a Government of Canada department or agency that aligns with their personal interests and career objectives. The majority of work placements are based in Iqaluit.", "Program Type/Target": "Education, Training, and Employment", "Cash to In-Kind Spectrum": "Service", "Method of Access": "Self Initiated - Form", "Mode of Access": "Email administrator", "Income Tested?": "No", "Major Eligibility Conditions": "Indigenous", "Other Eligibility Conditions": "Indigenous—recognized by Inuit Land Claim Association", "Documents required": "", "T5007 issued?": "No", "Is tax filing a requirement?": "No", "Taxable income?": "Yes", "2016/2017 Budget": "", "2016/2017 Number of recipients": "", "2017/2018 Budget": "", "2017/2018 Number of recipients": "", "2018/2019 budget": "", "2018/2019 Number of Recipients": "", "2019/2020 Budget": "", "2019/2020 Recipients": "", "2020/2021 budget": "", "2021/2022 budget": "", "2021/2022 Recipients": "", "Website": "https://www.cannor.gc.ca/eng/1386010541881/1386010818127", "Notes": ""}
